\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The OpenCode agent should be instructed to:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Understand the issue and inspect relevant code.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Implement a candidate fix.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Run the most relevant repository-visible tests.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Analyse failures rather than stopping at the first implementation.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Modify the implementation in response to test evidence.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	6	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Repeat until the relevant tests pass or a stopping condition is reached.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	7	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Avoid weakening, deleting, or bypassing tests to create an artificial pass.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	8	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Leave the best valid implementation in the working tree.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The agent does not need to create formal research, planning, or review documents.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Stopping conditions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The feedback loop should stop when one of the following occurs:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Relevant tests pass\
\ls10\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Maximum repair iterations are reached\
\ls10\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Runtime budget is exhausted\
\ls10\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Model cost or token budget is exhausted\
\ls10\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The same failure repeats without meaningful progress\
\ls10\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Repository commands repeatedly fail for environmental reasons\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 A simple initial limit could be:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf0 max_repair_cycles: 5\
max_runtime_minutes: 45\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 The exact values can be adjusted after the first runs.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Stagnation rule\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Treat the loop as stalled when:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The same tests fail with materially identical errors across multiple cycles\
\ls11\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The agent alternates between equivalent patches\
\ls11\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The number of failing tests does not decrease\
\ls11\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
No meaningful repository change is produced\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 When stalled, the agent should attempt one alternative strategy. If that also fails, it should terminate and preserve the best valid state reached.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

